               <head type="stepTitle" xml:lang="en">Post process and interpret the data. 1: Stray light
            substraction / Baseline correction.</head>
               <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en">
                  <p>Straylight correction (dark substraction)
              Baseline correction - Substraction of the fluorescence background from the
              spectra.</p>
                  <p>Possible source of error: <list>
                        <item>Fluorescence is the most commonly encountered issue when working with
                  conventional Raman spectroscopy. For cultural heritage applications, it can be due
                  to organic materials with chromophore groups or to inclusions and impurities in
                  some mineral compounds.</item>
                        <item>Some new equipment have algorithm for automatic background substraction, this
                  should be specified.</item>
                     </list>
                  </p>
               </desc>
